caption.text:
Jogja Jogja, Jogja Istimewa~

Sudah banyak yang membuat tulisan panjang tentang bagaimana Jogja layak untuk dicintai. Jogja menjadi rumah kedua yang selalu ingin dikunjungi kembali, sekedar menikmati Jalan Kaliurang yang tak pernah sepi, atau mencoba tempat atau atraksi baru untuk ambil foto-foto bergaya terkini.

Bukan sekedar tentang biaya hidup yang murah, karena kebahagiaan tidak sekedar tentang materi. Sebuah kota menjadi rumah karena telah dirajut banyak kisah yang dalam hati selalu terpatri.

Jog, tetap istimewa, ya.

One of the happiest timeline in my life was when I spent three years of craziness with this fellas. And yes, also when we meet again, and go crazy together again.

Dulu ga ada yang jilbaban, sekalinya reuni kayak geng pengajian... (btw yang kecil sendiri itu adeknya Yolanda. Belom, kami belum punya anak.)

caption.text:
I have revealed many failures, but this one is what almost always make me feel ashamed but now I'll confess: I am single since birth. And sometimes, it makes me feel like a failure. I started to point out that I'm overweight, that I'm ugly, that I can't dress up and make up properly. I am not attractive. But then I realized, maybe it's an opportunity for me to do many activities, to reach out wider network, to find who I really am so I would be ready and whole--not only following what someone wants from me before I discover my true soul. I also learn to be grateful for little things that can make me smile, so when the time comes, I can remember that we can't depend happiness only to someone. That's how I accept my failure, and learn to love myself. -- We think experience is our best teacher, failure is the best lesson. Have you ever thought that they can also be a great learning for other people?

Elefate.co (@elefate.co) is a collaborative media dedicated to redefine failure as opportunity to learn, for everyone. Let's help us build a supportive community that accept failure as valuable lesson that worth to be shared. We invite you to tell your story and let people learn from you. We invite you to learn from someone's story and appreciating their bravery.

Tag your friend and let's elefate together!

caption.text:
Dear Alpha Centauri,

Sebelum hari pertama kalian bertugas berakhir, aku pengen ngasih tau beberapa hal juga, mirip-mirip konsepnya tapi beda buat anak-anakku kemaren.

Yang pertama, aku sayang kalian. Maaf kalo jarang keliatan, tapi aku nggak bohong. Walau aku sudah jadi prede bacot yang banyak minta dan dikit bantu, sebenarnya alasanku cuma satu: aku tahu kalian bisa melakukan banyak hal yang lebih keren dari Andakara, dan aku pengen kalian belajar dari masa transisi untuk ga berada di bayang-bayang kami. Tiap masa ada pemimpinnya, tiap pemimpin ada masanya. Ini waktu kalian membuktikan bahwa bukan hanya memaksimalkan legacy, tapi juga membuat legacy-legacy yang lebih baik dalan delapan bulan untuk selamanya yang kalian miliki.

Yang kedua, selamat. Selamat memiliki keluarga baru, dan jangan melupakan keluarga yang lama. Selamat mendapatkan kesempatan mengubah hal-hal yang udah ngegemesin salahnya, selamat mendapatkan kesempatan untuk mewujudkan mimpi kalian yang mewakili mimpi entity. Selamat berkarya dengan ide-ide yang selalu menyala. Kata-kata "it's not going to be easy it's going to be worth it" udah mainstream, jadi pesanku nyontek pesan kak @tikabaswara dulu: don't forget to have fun.

Yang ketiga, terima kasih sudah bersedia mengemban tanggung jawab ini. Teman-teman dan adik-adik mempercayai kalian, kami semua mempercayai kalian. Waktunya kalian mempercayai diri sendiri--dan anggota-anggota yang kalian miliki.

Love,
Your used-to-be President.

#continuethelegacy #indonesiaisahome

Hai, anak-anakku.

Akhirnya datang juga ya, hari terakhir aku jadi mamak kalian (tapi kata Devina lebih mirip nenek karena sering sakit, tq dev) -- terlepas dari mau mamak atau nenek, ada beberapa hal yang pengen aku sampaikan.

Yang pertama, iyalah, apalagi kalo bukan makasih! Makasih buat kerja? Nggak. Kerja mah bukan buat aku, tapi buat peace and fulfillment of humankind potential--azek--jadi aku gaperlu makasih buat itu. Tapi makasih buat bertahan di tim ini, bertahan bareng aku, dan membentuk tim yang kuat dan keren. Makasih udah jadi anak-anak mandiri dan membanggakan. Everyone of you is unique and had proven me how bright you are in your own way. You guys are inspiration.

Yang kedua, maap ye. Aku bukan leader yang tracking bitch, tapi juga bukan yang romantis suka kasih kata-kata manis. Cenderung cuek, jarang kasih apresiasi pula... semoga aku masih punya strength dalam memimpin, yang kupikir adalah jadi tempat konsultasi tentang masalah dan ngasih space buat belajar bareng (amin). Moga2 kalian belajar sesuatu dari segala kekuranganku. üòÇ oya, maaf juga kalo perhatianku mgkn kerasa ga sama rata. Tapi sayangnya rata kok ‚ù§

Yang ketiga, tolonglah, jangan mellow-mellow banget. Grup andakara masih boleh dipake, masih boleh dikasih lelucon2 garingnya wyllson dan manda, yezki boleh curhat ttg departemen baru, anin dan  devina ttg jodoh dan kkn, fian tentang magang atau exposurenya, elory tentang perjalanan ke belandanya, nisa dan manda buat kegiatan baru after aiesec life yg masih belum diputuskan, rio wyllson raro dhanti yang curhat skripsi, dan aku curhat pengangguran. Jangan dikacangin ye kalo non-aiesec talks muncul di grup. Kita terbentuk karna AIESEC, tapi ga boleh berakhir karena AIESEC juga.

Yang keempat, selamat menempuh hidup baru! Disini kalian menempa diri buat bisa melakukan hal-hal ajaib, sekarang waktunya kalian melakukan lebih banyak hal ajaib lagi di luar sana. Segala macem perubahan fase hidup kabar-kabarin di grup, yah. üòô

Aku yakin pertemanan dan persodaraan kita lebih kuat kok daripada durasi kontrak jabatan UKM Kepemimpinan Universitas Gadjah Mada ini.

Dah, gitu.

Jangan sedih-sedih ya. Love you.

Ya, ruangannya berantakan, penuh meja dan kursi.

Tapi juga penuh kebahagiaan.

Bagi saya sendiri, hari itu juga penuh dengan rasa syukur. Rasa syukur telah memiliki orang-orang ini di dalam tim besar organisasi yang saya pimpin, rasa syukur telah melihat senyum mereka dan euforia mereka mengupload foto-foto di dunia maya.

Berada di posisi ini penuh dengan tantangan, namun dengan kerja nyata dan dedikasi mereka untuk berkarya, semuanya terasa lebih menyenangkan. Dari awal mula tahun kepengurusan, saya berjanji hasil kesuksesan saya adalah anggota yang nyaman dan 'bernyawa', bukan menjadi sekumpulan robot yang tidak tahu apa yang tengah dikerjakan.

Masih banyak tugas untuk satu semester ke depan; namun bersama mereka, saya yakin kesuksesan AIESEC UGM bisa diwujudkan bersama.

Ini cerita saya. 
Yuk, berbagi ceritamu juga!

caption.text:
Hi everyone, I humbly present you my amazing team. A support system, a family, anything I could ask for.

Our name is Andakara. Means the sun, and the philosophy works as we want to radiates warmth. And it has been done a good job so far. Seeing happy and developing members, how they are proud to be a part of this generation, to be a part of this organization, how they work so hard even to the new members layer, and how they actively speak up to give inputs to make the whole organization better--making me realized what makes this organization beautiful.

It is, simply, the feeling it gives.

The chance it provides, for anyone who's brave enough to find his/her true self in the stage of leading others. All the package of ups and downs make it a beautiful experience. And this experience enables me to meet these people, with all the warmth they radiates, an open hand and understanding of our limit, an appreciation of little things we do everyday, and available shoulders of empowerment to each other.

Andakara, it's not I'm being fluffy, I am just being honest: I am blessed to have you as a part of my life.

caption.text:
Living in a family that have three daughters, I believe that a part of women empowerment is having a freedom from violence. I am so grateful that our parents let us choose who we want to become, and always encourage us to be responsible for every decisions we took.

We wouldn't be able to grow if our rights to choose what we believed in got violated, even by verbally.

But not every woman has the priviledge to experience it. Violences are everywhere; verbally, physically, sexually. It's so terrifying because it can isolates them to maximize their potential. 
Women's Global Leadership Institute has announced that 25th of November is International Day for Elimination of Violence against Woman.

I support @bergerakpositif.id and invite everyone around the world to raise your voice by also using this twibbon:
https://www.isupportcause.com/campaign/bergerak-positif "Violence against women and girls is a human rights violation, public health pandemic and serious obstacle to sustainable development. It imposes large-scale costs on families, communities and economies. The world cannot afford to pay this price." ‚Äî Ban Ki-moon, UN Secretary-General.

Stop violence, be aware and be beware about it, and lets help those who are held victim for a better life. 
Let's spread out the words.

Apakah kemiskinan adalah sebuah pilihan?

Bagi banyak orang di sana: tidak. Tapi jelas, kamu bisa memilih untuk tidak mengalaminya.

Mari memilih. Untuk tidak hanya menggerutu tentang bagaimana mindset masyarakat terhadap kemiskinan, karena kamu adalah bagian dari masyarakat. Mari memilih. Untuk bukan hanya memperkaya diri sendiri, namun mulai peka untuk peduli.

Bersiaplah untuk didengarkan. Kenali orang-orang yang memiliki visi sejalan. Bersama menjadi bagian dari perubahan yang kamu inginkan.

Indonesia membutuhkanmu. Yogyakarta menunggumu.

caption.text:
Ngga full team sih, tapi cukup representatif untuk mewakilkan kegilaan dan keberisikan dalam dinamika brainstorming bareng.

Belum apa-apa udah sayang.

Cie.

Bully can be happened everywhere, including in cyber world. 
According to UNICEF studies, most young people run to their friends when receiving cyberbully. As a person who has ever experienced it in the firsthand, it was also happened in me. I had no idea how to tell my parents the reason why I cried all night for several days and refusing to eat--it was hella hard to explain that my internet peers spread hatred towards me and make it viral by putting specific hashtag to talk about me. It was viral and I suddenly had no friends in that circle. Even people who didn't know me hated me because everyone else do so.

It was 2010 and 6 years has passed. I forgave, I grew, but somehow the trauma has never fully left. Sometimes I'm still be anxious and uncomfortable whenever people posted something about how they dislike someone... I often assume it is me they are talking about. I often assume it is me people dislikes and hates. And yes, it's not healthy. 
I am coping with this but I don't want it to happen to anybody else.

Therefore, I support #ReplyForAll campaign initiated by @UNICEF. Fight cyberbully. #ENDviolence. Spread the word.

caption.text: Artjog9: Universal Influence.

An end is only another beginning.

For generation 1516, thank you so much for delivering amazing experiences that challenge generation 1617 to create continuity.

Special thank you for my lovely Flashlight Team, and of course our VP, Ester Margaretha who never cease to unleash the potential of her team members. Your leadership insipires me a lot. To Wildan and Hida, two warriors of Humanizer I never forget to be grateful of having in this term, thank you for always be there and not only become a professional team, but also a brother, a sister. For every members of Flashlight, thank you for all the supports through ups and downs... I love you. Good luck for any journey you'll take after AIESEC life, I am so thankful of having you as a part of my life. 
Another huge love and warm hugs for my new team, Andakara, Executive Board of AIESEC UGM 1617. I believe in you all, I believe in us, I believe that we would make a champion team. Let's live in our name, Andakara--the sun--let's radiates warmth and lighten up our society. Let's be purposeful Indonesia youths, who insipires the world by our passion and contribution. The journey will not be easy, but it's gonna be worth it. The responsibility is not something we should celebrate for, but a new family is truly something I am grateful for. And family never let each other down. Let's be solid, strong, and empowering.

Bismillahirrahmanirrahim. 
#StoriesWeMade #AIESECIndonesia

What could be nicer than knowing your bestfriend is your long-lost sister?

caption.text:
When AIESECers hang out together: "Sorry for all the problems." "No it's not a problem, it's a challenge!" "Exactly, challenge that will develop us." -- "You'll find a way to be together, you're both leaders that has solution-oriented quality! And by having a boyfie from different country, you'll be a true world citizen!" "And we're gonna empower others that things gonna work." "And it started from being self-aware that you both love each other!" -- And in every AIESEC keywords we teased to each other, we laughed. Or even in every time we talk, we laughed.

Thank you, Saori Hata, for all the laughters and good vibes. It has been a super happy day even when we faced so-called-'challenges' before finally heading up to the Ice Cream Parlour. I'm gonna miss you--or I'm gonna fly to Japan to meet you someday! :")

Thank you @anggieam @fitrihan @prillageonestri for inviting me join this #20factsofme, 'ere we go:
1) I have written this challenge but it was always failing when I uploaded. I found out mine was excess, Instagram has limit of caption to be below 2200characters. 
2) I haven't copied it so I was kzl.
3) I have a cute family. My father is a workaholic but also a family man. He woke me up by hugging and tickling me.
4) My mother is the best cook on earth.
5) I have the coolest older sister who never cease to inspire me. A graduate from UI's Accounting program.
6) My little sister is an amazing nerd. She reads popular Cassanda Clare's, Veronica Roth's, John Green's, etc's originally printed in English by the age of 13 (or she started at 12? I forget.). I only read teenlits by her age. Ouche.
7) I have a desire to travel the world to do something more than vacation.
8) A never-give-up abroad scholarship opportunity seeker although I had dramatic rough experiences about them.
9) A loyal fangirl of foods.
10) A proud ENFP. Find out more about it, it's really relevant with me.
11) Have sanguine personality traits.
12) Was once socially awkward, but now I try to be a social butterfly instead. I think I worked it out.
13) The perks of being a social butterfly: can easily talk to strangers and make new friends.
14) The risks of being a social butterfly: the friendship rarely deep enough to be the one I can count on to.
15) My mom wanted me to be a doctor but I went to International Relations major instead. I promised her to have a doctor for her son-in-law. (Aamiin?) But doesn't mean I block non-doctor guys.
16) Living in two parallel universe since 2009. Another one is roleplay text based universe.
17) I circle country areas I have visited on the world map I sticked on my bedroom wall.
18) I love children. I'm going to work for UNICEF. Or Walt Disney. That sounds like a promise? Yes it does.
19) Never had a boyfriend and still not intended to. I want to be a wife.
20) I copied this caption before upload it because of point 1. It feels traumatic. 
For those who I tag, please tell the world #20facts of you! Have fun :D
